  "prompt": "What are the symptoms of a heart cancer?",
  "response": "Heart cancer (primary cardiac tumor) is extremely rare, and symptoms can vary depending on the type and location of the tumor. Some potential symptoms include:\n\n1. Chest pain or pressure\n2. Shortness of breath\n3. Irregular heartbeat\n4. Sudden heart failure\n5. Fatigue\n6. Fever\n7. Unexplained weight loss\n8. Swelling in legs or abdomen\n9. Fainting or dizziness\n10. Heart murmurs\n\nHowever, it's important to note:\n- Primary heart cancer is very rare\n- Most heart tumors are actually secondary (metastatic) cancers\n- Symptoms often mimic other heart conditions\n- Definitive diagnosis requires medical imaging and tests\n\nIf you experience persistent cardiac symptoms, consult a healthcare professional for proper evaluation and diagnosis.",
